        "timestamp": "2020-10-06 08:00:44.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 10:\n\n> Patch Set 10: Code-Review-1\n> \n> (1 comment)\n> \n> As makefile/scripts are intended for dynamic override under OOM deployment specifically, wondering if these should be hosted under OOM (under contrib possibly). Although the current usage is specific to VEScollector,  configmap created could be used by other components needing access to external schemas. \n> \n> Let me know if any strong reason to maintain this under ves repo.\n\nOk, we`d try to place these scripts in the OOM. Essentially, the ONAP operator will have the OOM contents by default on the RKE node, and there would be no reason to check the VES repo out to get these scripts. Still, I`d like to keep this in Guilin release. OOM has not branched yet, if we contribute this script now, it will be come part of Guilin anyway.\n\nCreated OOM-2589 to cover that one.",
